James Rising received an email from Nishat Jarin, expressing her interest in pursuing a PhD in Sustainable Development, Circular Economy, and Climate Change under his guidance. She highlighted her excellent academic performance, relevant experience, and commitment to interdisciplinary solutions for sustainability. In response, James drafted a professional email thanking her for her interest but informing her that there is no funding available for new PhD students this year. He encouraged her to explore other funding opportunities and invited her to schedule a Zoom meeting to discuss her research interests further, providing a link for easy scheduling.
